# Health & Readiness checks for all three services
# Run these first to confirm the stack is up before testing flows.
# Expected: all return 200. If any return 503, that service isn't ready yet.




### orders-api — liveness
GET {{ordersApiUrl}}/healthz

### orders-api — readiness (checks Postgres + Redis)
GET {{ordersApiUrl}}/readyz

### orders-api — Prometheus metrics
GET {{ordersApiUrl}}/metrics

### orders-api — OpenAPI spec (paste into https://editor.swagger.io to browse)
GET {{ordersApiUrl}}/openapi/v1.json

### checkout-bff — livenes
GET {{checkoutBffUrl}}/healthz

### checkout-bff — readiness (checks orders-api + Redis)
GET {{checkoutBffUrl}}/readyz

### checkout-bff — Prometheus metrics
GET {{checkoutBffUrl}}/metrics

### notifier-worker — liveness (also checks heartbeat staleness)
GET {{notifierWorkerUrl}}/healthz

### notifier-worker — readiness (checks Redis connection + consumer group joined)
GET {{notifierWorkerUrl}}/readyz

### notifier-worker — service info (version, consumer_id, consumer_group)
GET {{notifierWorkerUrl}}/info

### notifier-worker — Prometheus metrics (consumer lag is the primary SLI)
GET {{notifierWorkerUrl}}/metrics
